==Summary==
{{Information
|Description = Dick, Kerr & Co were commissioned to build 100 of these locomotives by the military for use on the trench railways. They comprised a 45hp petrol engine and a DC generator, which in turn drove 2 DC electric motors. This photo taken during construction was released in 1919.
|Source = '''Original publication''': Photo was taken in 1914-1918 period<br/>
'''Immediate source''': The Model Engineer & Electrician, April 3rd 1919, page 225
|Date = 1914 to 1918
|Author = Unknown<br/>
(Life time: Unknown)
